{"lemma":"حَمّاماتٌ","slug":"حَمّاماتٌ","root":"ح.م.م","root_slug":"ح-م-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-م-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":3,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9001","n9002","n9003","n9012"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%91%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a bath, a bathtub; a bathhouse, a spa","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a bath, a bathtub; a washroom; a bathroom; a restroom","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a watering hole","tags":["countable","dated"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"doves, pigeons","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"death (the cessation of life)","tags":["literary","poetic"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ح م م (ḥ m m); related to heating.\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *šawmān-."},"ipa":["/ħam.maːm/","/ħa.maːm/","/ħi.maːm/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9001","headword_ar":"حَمَامٌ","root":"Hm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pigeon,"},{"kind":"text","text":"both"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"domestic,"},{"kind":"text","text":"but more properly the former; and sometimes not strictly confined to denote the pigeon-kind:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain wild bird, that does not keep to the houses; well-known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any collared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ringed, bird;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) so with the Arabs;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAxit","text_ar":"فَوَاخِت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamaAriY~","text_ar":"قَمَارِىّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saAqu Hur~","text_ar":"سَاقُ حُرّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTaA","text_ar":"قَطَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waraA$iyn","text_ar":"وَرَاشِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb,) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"domestic"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pigeons"},{"kind":"text","text":"] ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~awaAjin","text_ar":"الدَّوَاجِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"), also, (El-Umawee, S, Msb,) that are taken into houses for the purpose of producing their young ones; (El-Umawee, S;) to which last alone the term is applied by the vulgar: accord. to Ks, it is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"species"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yamaAm","text_ar":"يَمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"is that which keeps to the houses: accord. to As, the latter is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAm waHo$iY~","text_ar":"حَمَام وَحْشِىّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild pigeon"},{"kind":"text","text":"];"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of the birds of the desert:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) or, accord. to Esh-Sháfi'ee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmN","text_ar":"حَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any kind of bird that drinks in the manner denoted by the verb"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eab~a","text_ar":"عَبَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"continuously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and cooes; including the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamaAriY~","text_ar":"قَمَارِىّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waraA$iyn","text_ar":"وَرَاشِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawaAxit","text_ar":"فَوَاخِت"},{"kind":"text","text":";"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether it be, or be not, collared,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ringed; domestic"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wild:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the flesh"},{"kind":"page_break","n":637},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thereof strengthens the venereal faculty, and increases the seminal fluid and the blood; the putting it, cut open while alive, upon the place stung by a scorpion, is a proved cure; and the blood stops bleeding from the nose:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) the n. un. is with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb;) which is applied to the male and the female: (S Msb, K:) and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmN","text_ar":"حَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", because the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is added to restrict to unity, not to make fem.: (S:) but to distinguish the masc., you may say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu HamaAmFA EalaY HamaAmapK","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ حَمَامًا عَلَى حَمَامَةٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw a male"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pigeon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon a female"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"pigeon"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Zj, Msb:) accord. to ISd and the K, however,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmN","text_ar":"حَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"should not be applied to the [single] male: (TA:) in a verse of Homeyd Ibn-Thowr, cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hur~N","text_ar":"حُرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", by the n. un. is meant"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumoriy~ap","text_ar":"قُمْرِيَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":": the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HmAmp","text_ar":"حمامة"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmN","text_ar":"حَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) [or rather this is the coll. gen. n.,] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAy^imu","text_ar":"حَمَايِمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmaAtN","text_ar":"حَمَامَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) and sometimes"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAmN","text_ar":"حَمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as a sing.: [so in an ex. above: and] Jirán-el-'Owd says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"wa*ak~araniY AlS~ibaA baEoda Alt~anaAy^iY\n                      \n                     \n                        HamaAmapu A^ayokapK tadoEuw HamaAmaA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And a female pigeon of a thicket, calling a male pigeon, reminded me of youth, after estrangement"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: a poet also says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"HamaAmaA qaqorapK waqaEaA faTaAraA"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two pigeons of a desert tract alighted and flew away"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and El-Umawee cites, as an ex. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamaAm","text_ar":"حَمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to the domestic [pigeons],"},{"kind":"quote","text":"qawaATinFA mak~apa mino wuroqi AlHamaY"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inhabiting Mekkeh, of the pigeons of a white colour inclining to black"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHmY","text_ar":"الحمى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or rather it should be written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamaA","text_ar":"الحَمَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"] meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamaAm","text_ar":"الحَمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.)"}],"source_refs":["ISd","K","S","Msb","Az","TA","Zj"]},{"entry_id":"n9002","headword_ar":"حُمَامٌ","root":"Hm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fever"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~aY","text_ar":"حُمَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of camels;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~aA='u","text_ar":"حُمَّا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of all beasts,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"including camels:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) accord. to ISh, when camels eat date-stones, [which are often given to them as food,] they are [sometimes] affected with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumaAm","text_ar":"حُمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qumaAH","text_ar":"قُمَاح"},{"kind":"text","text":"; the former of which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a heat affecting the skin, until the body is smeared with mud,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clay, in consequence of which they forsake the abundant herbage, and their fat goes away; and it continues in them a month, and then passes away."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Az, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HumaAmu qur~K","text_ar":"حُمَامُ قُرٍّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The disease termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muwm","text_ar":"مُوم"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which affects men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiymN","text_ar":"حَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A noble chief,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lord:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) thought by Az to be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"humaAmN","text_ar":"هُمَامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","K"]},{"entry_id":"n9003","headword_ar":"حِمَامٌ","root":"Hm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see its syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hum~apN","text_ar":"حُمَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; of which it is also a pl. (K.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n9012","headword_ar":"حَمَّامٌ","root":"Hm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A hot bath;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain structure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;) so called because it occasions sweating, or because of the hot water that is in it; accord. to ISd, derived from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamiymu","text_ar":"الحَمِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dayomaAsN","text_ar":"دَيْمَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) of the masc. gender, (Mgh, K,) and fem. also, (Mgh,) generally the latter; (Msb;) but some say that it is a mistake to make it fem., (MF, TA,) though IB cites a verse in which a fem. pronoun is asserted to refer to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hm~Am","text_ar":"حمّام"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ham~aAmaAtN","text_ar":"حَمَّامَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, K;) accord. to Sb, [not because the sing. is fem., but] because, though masc., it has no broken pl. (TA.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamiymN","text_ar":"حَمِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","Mgh","MF","TA"]}]}}